proof.p:
Consider Q^TQ = [m_{i,j}]. Then
m_{i,j} = \vec{q}_i\cdot\vec{q}_j = \begin{cases}0\amp i\neq j\\1\amp i=j, \end{cases}
and the desired result holds.

algorithm.p:
Given the m\times n inconsistent system of equations represented by A\vec{x}=\vec{b}, let QR=A be the full QR factorization of A and let

    \hat{R} \amp = \text{ upper \(n\times n\) submatrix of \(R\) }
    \hat{\vec{d}} \amp = \text{ upper \(n\) entries of } \vec{d}=Q^T\vec{b}
